          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεδνός</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καδ, κήδω</span>), sup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεδνότατος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">careful, true, good,
            excellent;</span> a poetic synonym of <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγαθός,
            ἐσθλός</span>, used mostly of persons; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεδνὰ ϝιδυῖα</span>, ‘careful-minded,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 1.428</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
